# ============================================================================
# Types Module Configuration
# ============================================================================

config TYPES
	bool "Enable Types Module"
	default y
	help
	  Core types module provides common type definitions used across
	  multiple core modules (PCL, PDL, etc.).

	  This module contains only type definitions and has no runtime code.
	  It exists to break circular dependencies between PCL and PDL.

	  Dependency relationship:
	  - PCL depends on TYPES (uses config types)
	  - PDL depends on TYPES (uses config types)
	  - PDL depends on PCL (uses config data)
	  - Result: PCL→TYPES←PDL, PDL→PCL (no circular dependency)
